f=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4576.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://tang123.homestead.com/files/personalpic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Upgrading my equipment(lvl 60 warlord)</span><hr size=1> Myrmidon's legs are better than Warlord's because they have 40 hp instead of the 0 hp of the warlord's. The myrmidon's and warlord's bp are nearly identical and i'd take whichever you can get first.<br>
<br>
If you can afford a Fleshgrinder (12/19 75 hps 160dd proc), I would put that mainhand and Frostbringer offhand for a nice dps/taunt combination. I wouldn't really recommend the swiftblade of zek, it does have nice hps and decent dps, but without a proc it's not really the end all be all of weapons.<br>
<br>
Also, if you worship Rallos Zek or The Tribunal, you can check out the heraldic armors that are often for sale in the bazaar. I'm not sure of the Tribunal version but the Rallos Zek version is called Fierce Heraldic. The HPs on the deity armor are quite nice if you can wear it. Farming HoT is probably your best bet if you are short on cash though.<br>
<br>
edit: your best bet on 40-41% haste item would be to do dozekar quests if you can manage to take him down, and get either the cloak of the firestorm, silver bracelet of speed, or (ick) serrated dragon tooth. I don't really like the serrated dragon tooth because it has 0 hps and these days is quite a burden for me having no hit points in that slot. <p>Kamiccolo<br>
